["
When we create a child under a component which is a parent the new item comes under this
but when we create it along side a child it is another item under the same branch
Isn't this the expected way?
https://github.com/trimble-oss/modus-web-components/assets/122255626/dfb746c7-5448-4250-b2fa-f1c04bab45b5

", 'Can we get a code snippet that adds the new item as a child instead of a sibling so we can verify how its currently working in this regard?  Possibly a code pen, but can just be pasted here as an example script.', "> Can we get a code snippet that adds the new item as a child instead of a sibling so we can verify how its currently working in this regard? Possibly a code pen, but can just be pasted here as an example script.
``` 
  addButton.addEventListener('buttonClick', () => {
      const nodeId =
        container.querySelectorAll('modus-tree-view-item').length + 1;
      const selectedItems = root.selectedItems;
      if (nodeId) {
        const selectedItemId =
          selectedItems && selectedItems.length > 0 ? selectedItems[0] : null;
        const selectedItemElement = querySelect(selectedItemId);
        const selectedItemParent = selectedItemElement?.parentElement;
        const newNode = document.createElement('modus-tree-view-item');
        newNode.nodeId = nodeId;
        newNode.editable = true;
        const insertParent = selectedItemParent || root;
        const insertBeforeElement =
          selectedItemElement || root.firstElementChild;
        insertBeforeElement.appendChild(newNode);
      }
    });
```
The code snippet in the storybook for adding a node does `insertBefore` to the parent node
`insertParent.insertBefore(newNode, insertBeforeElement);`
 the other way to add it as a child is to use `appendChild` 
 `insertBeforeElement.appendChild(newNode);`
in that case the childNode or the new node is getting appended only if the selected node is a parent node already so we cannot convert a node who is not a parent before appending to a parent.


here is codepen to demonstrate the difference
https://codepen.io/Elisha-Sam-Peter-Prabhu/pen/RwmRrwY?editors=1111
**(NOTE: The `insertParent.insertBefore(newNode, insertBeforeElement);` code is commented by default )**", "@ElishaSamPeterPrabhu Based on your codepen, seems the defect is that we aren't handling the addition of children properly.  That would be what needs to be fixed to resolve this ticket.  If adding a child, it should end up in a state that matches how it would be if it was originally defined that way.", "> @ElishaSamPeterPrabhu Based on your codepen, seems the defect is that we aren't handling the addition of children properly. That would be what needs to be fixed to resolve this ticket. If adding a child, it should end up in a state that matches how it would be if it was originally defined that way.

Yes, we don't support adding children to the items now.", 'To resolve, we need to handle a child being added to an item, and updating the parent correctly so they can expand/collapse.  
- Item has no children, child added, new parent now can expand/collapse
- Item has children, all children removed, parent no longer can expand/collapse
- Item has children, children added, parent is not affected.']

